Globe and Mail in the morning, quiet night, comfy bed, lots of pillows...and a breakfast buffet that was excellent and cheaper than some.	The bed was a king and was soft and comfortable and there was no noise to be heard in the halls or other rooms.	Room was quiet and could not hear people in rooms next door but could hear people speaking in the hallway.	There are also a good variety of cheap/ethnic eateries up and down Yonge St. As busy as this area is, we didn't hear any traffic noise and slept well on very comfortable beds.